A widely-recognized lawyer and natural leader, clients rely on Pierre for his seamless service and ability to navigate complex strategies.
As National leader of our Africa Group, Quebec Leader of the Global Metals & Mining Group, counsel in the firm’s Business Law Group and former Managing Partner of the firm’s Quebec City office, clients benefit from Pierre’s versatility and leadership. With a diversified practice focused on mergers and acquisitions, private equity and related commercial matters, Pierre’s knowledge expands across several industries, most notably mining, oil and gas and energy on both a domestic and international scale, notably in sub-Saharan Africa.
Clients view Pierre as a trusted advisor and he is notably known for his ability to form relationships with many significant players at all levels of government within Africa, most notably sub-Saharan Africa. His strong presence on this continent is evidenced by his impressive client base. For example, Pierre has recently assisted clients in the Ivory Coast, Burkina Faso, Madagascar, Senegal, Guinea, and Morocco.

#### Pierre’s wide-range of experience is evidenced by his representation notably of:
- Rio Tinto Iron, Titanium & Diamonds in the negotiation of a new fiscal regime for their mining projects in Madagascar;
- 8 Capital as the co-lead of an 80 million dollar financing of Aya Gold & Silver for their mining projects in Morocco;
- Rabaska (a partnership of Energir, Enbridge and Engie) in an asset transaction involving Investissement Québec and the Port of Québec;
- Roxgold Sango in their negotiation of new mining agreements in the Ivory Coast;
- Endeavour Mining in the context of negotiations of their mining titles with the Government of Senegal;
- Resource Capital Funds in relation to the debt financing of the construction of Orezone Gold Corporation’s gold mine in Burkina Faso;
- Teranga Gold in their acquisition from Rangold of the Massawa gold project in Senegal and negotiations with the government of Senegal representatives;
- IamGold with regard to mining convention negotiations in Senegal;
- Resource Capital Funds with regard to its acquisition of a minority participation in Orezone Gold Corporation in Burkina Faso;
- SRG Graphite with regard to mining projects in Guinea;
- Sama Resources Inc. with regard to a transaction with HPX-TechCo Inc. regarding a nickel mining project in the Ivory Coast;
- Teranga Gold in the acquisition of Gryphon Minerals Limited, a company involved in the mining sector in Burkina Faso;
- the Government of Madagascar with regard to the negotiation of hydro-electric projects under the direction of the African Legal Support Facility of the African Development Bank;
- Endeavour Mining regarding a gold project in Mali;
- Windiga Energy Inc., a company involved in the renewable energy sector in Africa;
- Teranga Gold in a negotiation of an overall agreement with the Government of Senegal regarding the Sabodala gold production project;
- Hydrocarbure Anticosti regarding an oil and gas project on Anticosti Island;
- RoxGold Inc. regarding a gold mine project in Burkina Faso;
- Managem, a Moroccan company involved in the mining sector, on different projects in Africa, notably in Guinea;
- GoviEx Uranium regarding a uranium mine project in Niger;
- several clients who are conducting oil and gas exploration activities in the Province of Quebec, as well as counsel to the Québec Oil and Gas Association;
- several clients involved in the mining industry including SOQUEM Inc, a subsidiary of the Investissement Québec, which operates in the mining sector;
- Gaz Métropolitain Inc. principal distributor of natural gas in the Province of Quebec, in the implementation of a $1-billion LNG receiving terminal project in Lévis, in partnership with Enbridge Inc. and Gaz de France within the Rabaska Partnership;
In addition to his legal practice, Pierre sits on several boards of directors, including that of Export Development Canada (EDC) and the Canada Development Investment Corporation (FinDev Canada). He is also Chair of the Board of Directors of PMET Resources, a member of the Board of Directors of the Canada‑Africa Chamber of Business, and serves on the Governance Committee of the Canadian Institute of Mining, Metallurgy and Petroleum (CIM). He is a graduate of the Institute of Corporate Directors (ICD) and also holds the ESG Global Competent Boards designation (GCB.D). Over the course of his career, Pierre has served as a moderator or speaker at numerous conferences in the fields of mining, oil and gas, and energy. He is a co-founder and has acted for more than ten years as a speaker and/or moderator at the Franco-Mine Conference in Cape Town (Mining Indaba) and in Toronto (PDAC). Pierre has been repeatedly recognized over the years as a leading Canadian lawyer in various fields and publications such as Who’s Who Legal Canada in the mining sector (Global Leader),Best Lawyers in Canada in Energy Regulatory Law, in the Canadian Legal Lexpert Directory in the mining, energy (electricity), oil and gas and corporate mid-market sectors, as well as in the Lexpert Special Editions of Leading Canadian Lawyers in various fields such as Global Mining, Cross-Border Corporate and Energy. Acritas Stars has recognized him as a standout lawyer and APL Energies has named him Personality of the year in 2019, a career achievement award in the energy sector in the province of Quebec. He is also the only Canadian lawyer listed in Chambers Global Guide as a Leading Lawyer in the area of Mining, International & Cross-Border, Africa-wide.
